go-openh264 — pure-Go H.264/AVC decoder (decoding only)
Copyright (c) 2026 Oleksandr Zhabotynskyi

This product includes software developed as a clean-room Go reimplementation of
an H.264/AVC decoder written from the ISO/IEC 14496-10 specification, with
structural reference to:

  * OpenH264 by Cisco Systems, Inc. — https://github.com/cisco/openh264
    Licensed under the BSD 2-Clause License (see the LICENSE file in this
    directory). Reference for CABAC, the High-profile 8x8 transform, and the
    context/threshold tables.

  * The ISO/IEC 14496-10 (H.264 / MPEG-4 Part 10) specification — the primary
    source of the bitstream syntax, the decoding processes and the
    variable-length-coding tables.

The BSD 2-Clause license text in the LICENSE file is reproduced from OpenH264 as
required for redistribution of BSD-licensed derived work.

